  <bioghist id="aspace_74c2d45df5156dcfa8e194340e82fc97">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Oliver H. Hewitt, 1916-1999, a resident of South Florida since 1971, was chief of research for the Canadian Wildlife Service from 1944-1950. He was a professor at Cornell teaching wildlife ecology from 1950-1971 when he retired as a wildlife consultant. The author of "Fieldbook of Birds of the Florida Suncoast," 1976, Hewitt worked as a columnist for the "Charlotte Sun Herald" as the author of "Fieldnotes."</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_6bafc5596a50631f2a02bd3dd0c88f17">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Correspondence to and from Oliver Hewitt from bird enthusiasts, transcripts of columns written for the Charlotte, Florida "Sun Herald."</p>  </scopecontent>
